{
  "texts": [
    "To identify significant deviations in term usage, we considered an absolute modified Z-score of 3.5 or higher as indicative of a meaningful increase or decrease 19",
    "The resulting dataset, containing the modified Z-scores for each term and year, was then used for further statistical analysis.",
    "A linear mixed-effects model was used to compare the usage of potentially AI-influenced terms and common academic phrases from 2000 to 2024.",
    "The data, consisting of modified Zscores for each word or phrase, were obtained and reshaped into a long format.",
    "The model, constructed using the 'lme' function from the 'nlme' package in R, included the modified Zscores as the dependent variable, the group (potentially AI-influenced terms or common academic phrases) as a fixed effect, and a random intercept for each word or phrase to account for repeated measures."
  ]
}